BSDKProcessingMode","abstract":[{"text":"Scanners typically can produce better results from a single image if they are allowed to spend a longer time analyzing it.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"On the other hand, scanners can produce even better results if they can analyze multiple images of the same subject and cross-check and combine the results.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The processing mode tells the scanner whether to optimize for single or multiple images of a subject.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"SBSDKProcessingMode","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SBSDKProcessingMode","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkprocessingmode","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKProcessingMode","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://net.doo.ScanbotSDK/documentation/ScanbotSDK/SBSDKProcessingMode/live":{"type":"topic","fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"live","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/net.doo.ScanbotSDK\/documentation\/ScanbotSDK\/SBSDKProcessingMode\/live","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/scanbotsdk\/sbsdkprocessingmode\/live","abstract":[{"text":"In live mode input images are expected to come from a video source like a camera.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Scanners in live mode typically spend little time on each image and are able to quickly analyze multiple images and combine the individual image results into a final result.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Individual results from a particular image may be less accurate than running the scanner in single-shot mode on that frame, but after aggregating a few images of the same subject, the final result becomes much more accurate.","type":"text"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SBSDKProcessingModeLive","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"SBSDKProcessingMode.live"}